  "description": "Correlate the hourly etcd snapshot CronJob (`talosctl etcd snapshot`) with etcd commit latency, apiserver responsiveness, and cilium-agent restarts. Built to test the TALOS-w4t hypothesis: 'does the snapshot fsync storm stall etcd long enough that cilium /healthz fails and triggers cascade?' Pairs with TALOS-r10 (Flux throttle hypothesis applied 2026-05-30) — the two hypotheses are complementary; this dashboard isolates the snapshot signal.\n\nIMPORTANT: etcd metrics may be missing if the alloy scrape config does not target the CP node :2381. The 'No Data' panels indicate that. See configs/nodes/controlplane.yaml — etcd is configured with listen-metrics-urls: http://0.0.0.0:2381 already; needs a prometheus.scrape stanza in alloy/helmrelease.yaml.",
