      "options": {
        "code": {"language": "plaintext", "showLineNumbers": false, "showMiniMap": false},
        "content": "## Verdict matrix\n\nThis dashboard is wired specifically to test the **TALOS-w4t** hypothesis:\n> The hourly `talosctl etcd snapshot` triggers an fsync storm on the CP's etcd, stalling the write path, timing out kube-apiserver's etcd client, failing cilium-agent /healthz, and cascading into the cluster-wide meltdown we kept seeing on 2026-05-29.\n\n### Reading the panels\n\n| What you see | What it means |\n|---|---|\n| etcd commit p99 stays flat (< 100ms) through snapshot annotations | TALOS-w4t REFUTED. Snapshot is innocent under current load. Look at TALOS-r10 (Flux throttle, applied 2026-05-30) and HA control plane (TALOS-arx). |\n| etcd commit p99 spikes 5-15s after each green snapshot annotation | TALOS-w4t CONFIRMED. Mitigations: move snapshot to a worker etcd peer (needs HA), throttle frequency from hourly to 4-6h, or relocate snapshot target to a faster disk. |\n| etcd commit stays flat but cilium restarts spike at clock-aligned times (`:00`, `:10`) | Look at TALOS-r10. Flux mass-reconcile is the more likely trigger. |\n| No data on etcd panels | **etcd metrics aren't scraped yet.** Talos exposes them at `:2381` on the CP (`listen-metrics-urls: http://0.0.0.0:2381` in `configs/nodes/controlplane.yaml`). Add a `prometheus.scrape` stanza in `infrastructure/base/monitoring/v2-otel/alloy/helmrelease.yaml` pointing at `192.168.1.54:2381`. Until then, fall back to the apiserver-latency panel + the snapshot Job duration panel. |\n| apiserver p99 climbs during the snapshot window | Whatever the cause, write path is stalling. Either etcd is the bottleneck (look at the panel above) or apiserver is CPU-starved on the single-CP. |\n\n### Reproduce on demand\n\n```sh\n./scripts/test-suspect-etcd-snapshot.sh\n# Takes ~3-5 min. Triggers one snapshot Job, measures baseline / during / after,\n# and prints a PASS/FAIL/UNKNOWN verdict + writes artifacts to .output/etcd-snapshot-probe/.\n```\n\n### Related work\n\n- **TALOS-w4t** — snapshot timing shift `:00 → :17` to disambiguate (this hypothesis)\n- **TALOS-r10** — Flux mass-reconcile throttle (applied 2026-05-30, observation window open)\n- **TALOS-arx** — HA control plane (removes single-CP fragility entirely)\n- **TALOS-fa7** — observability epic (this dashboard is one of the artifacts)\n\nPost-mortem: [docs/06-troubleshooting/2026-05-29-six-meltdowns-and-the-real-root-cause.md](https://github.com/TheBranchDriftCatalyst/talos-homelab/blob/main/docs/06-troubleshooting/2026-05-29-six-meltdowns-and-the-real-root-cause.md)",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "title": "Reading guide & verdict matrix",
      "transparent": false,
      "type": "text"
    }
